Identify and exploit an OS command injection vulnerability in the stock check feature.

Navigated to a product page
Clicked "Check Stock" and intercepted the request in Burp Suite
Observed the POST request to /product/stock with parameters:

  productId=1&storeId=1

The storeId parameter appeared to be passed directly to a shell command
No input sanitization was observed

Injected a command separator into storeId:

  productId=1&storeId=1|whoami

The response returned the output of whoami, confirming command injection

An attacker can execute arbitrary OS commands on the server
Potential for full server compromise, data exfiltration, reverse shells, etc.


